That analysis confirms what I suspected. Here's the real situation:\
\
Tagging alone won't work. The old-style atoms (nyc_executives, most of educators, gen_z anxiety/overwhelm) are fundamentally different prose \'97 40-70 words per block, flat escalation, no callbacks, behavioral shift only. The new-style atoms (healthcare_rns, gen_alpha_students, and the 4 educator files I just wrote) are 140-200 words per block with clear depth escalation, callback architecture, and epistemological identity shift.\
\
